12 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-26.1-11.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 43-26.1-11.1. Ordering imaging.
15 1. A physical therapist may order musculoskeletaldiagnostic imaging consisting of plain
16 film radiographs if the physical therapist holds:
17 a. Holds a clinical doctorate degree in physical therapy; or has completed
18 b. Completed a board-approved formal medical imaging training program.
19 2. A physical therapist ordering diagnostic imaging shall report the results to the patient's
20 designated specialty or primary care provider within seven days of receipt of the image
21 to ensure coordination of care, unless:
22 a. The patient does not have a specialty or primary care provider; or
23 b. The specialty or primary care provider received the images from the health care
24 professional who performed or interpreted the images.
